<h4>Kickstarter ...</h4>
[% FILTER html_para %]
Kickstarter will allow us to determine the global demand for this product, and give us a way to bridge
the gap between hand-built units and small-scale automated production in China. Yes, China.

If the demand is high, Paul will happily spend time in Shenzen getting the best value components
run through production, using project-specific testbed hardware to install the valid firmware
images and confirm the sanity of the manufacturing process (checking voltages as well as USB
communication and performance).

Now you see another reason for everyone to know how to validate their [% onerng %] devices;
there is no totally secure supply-chain on the planet for the truly paranoid. If you know
how to inspect the hardware and how to install your own firmware, you can mitigate so many
more potential weaknesses in the devices that you need to rely on.
[% END %]

